cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR

This paper is about comparing the accuracy and complexity of state-of-the-art CNN architectures for face and head detection in real-time video surveillance applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper compares the computational complexity of different architectures, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses datasets to evaluate the performance of the models, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of these architectures in practical real-time applications, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
